The paper discusses the topic of quantitative information flow (QIF) and proposes new notions of dynamic leakage based on entropy. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also involves the use of model counting tools for Boolean formulae, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and scalability of the proposed method, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
